description: For a new years eve I was asked to make a presentation on a random topic. I had no idea what to do so I made a script to generate slides with random stock images and quoes inspired by "Talking Points" from Jackbox Party 7. It's aimed to be rendered with [`Marp`](https://marp.app/)
An R Script to mirror ArcGIS Rest Service using sitemap
Rimworld output log published using HugsLib
Recursively walk a directory to a specified depth
دعم عربي/إنجليزي كامل تسجيل تلقائي للأحداث تقارير احترافية رسائل ملونة ومنظمة معلومات المطور والإيميل
ComfyUI custom node: Pixel Color Picker – extracts RGB/CMYK/alpha from specific pixel coords in an image batch, with preview crosshair and optional mask generation
Bazel rule for cross-platform shader compilation (HLSL to Metal, SPIR-V, DXIL) with cfg=exec
Bazel rule for multi-language Protobuf generation (C#, Rust, Python, Go) with cfg=exec for cross-compilation
ComfyUI custom node: Image Info With Source Dir – drag-and-drop images but recover original full path, filename, directory, and last-modified via hash matching
